 Introduction
 &lt;a href="#introduction" class="heading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink to this heading"&gt;🔗&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this challenge you will operate AI infrastructure the cloud native way. You will use
&lt;a href="https://meshery.io/"&gt;Meshery&lt;/a&gt; — the open-source cloud native manager — to import a
&lt;a href="https://docs.digitalocean.com/products/kubernetes/"&gt;DigitalOcean Kubernetes (DOKS)&lt;/a&gt; GPU cluster,
capture an LLM serving stack as a reusable &lt;strong&gt;Design&lt;/strong&gt;, deploy it, and &lt;strong&gt;performance-test&lt;/strong&gt; the
inference endpoint with a Meshery &lt;strong&gt;Performance Profile&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This mirrors how platform teams run model serving at scale: declarative designs, real-time cluster
